{"title":"Garmin Edge 1050 has a new shape and more social features including Garmin Pay and a bell","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/garmin-edge-1050","date":1719313646000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/garmin-edge-1050\">Garmin Edge 1050 has a new shape and more social features including Garmin Pay and a bell</a></p>\n\n<p>The new Garmin Edge 1050 breaks away from the steady progression seen in the top spec Edge 10x series computers. While the Edge 1040 had essentially the same format as the Edge 1030 Plus, the new Edge 1050 has a more squared-off shape, and Garmin has also added new features including a speaker that can act as a bike bell.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Garmin Edge 1050 is priced at £649.99, £20 more than the Edge 1040 Solar.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-it-s-better-without-gps\">Opinion: Cycling is better without GPS</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tutorials/turbo-trainer-workouts-to-improve-your-cycling\">Best turbo trainer workouts to make you a stronger cyclist</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-bike-computers-gps-computers-for-training-navigation-and-data\">Best bike computers with GPS 2024 for training, navigation and data reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/the-best-turbo-trainers-a-buyers-guide\">Best smart turbo trainers: Top Zwift compatible indoor trainers</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-praise-of-the-cafe-stop\">In praise of the cafe stop</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Shorter battery life, more colour</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"785\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-970x785.jpg\" alt=\"Garmin Edge 1050\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-970x785.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-300x243.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-768x622.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-1536x1243.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-2048x1658.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-750x607.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0014_Surface_Type_metric-1140x923.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Garmin quotes a battery life of 20 hours for the new<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/accessories/gps-bike-computers\" target=\"_blank\"> computer</a>. Again, that’s a break with its trend to offer longer and longer battery life on its premium computers and more in line with competitors from <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/wahoo-elemnt-roam-review\" target=\"_blank\">Wahoo </a>and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hammerhead-karoo-3\" target=\"_blank\">Hammerhead</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/garmin-edge-1040-solar-gps-bike-computer-review\" target=\"_blank\">Edge 1040</a> has a claimed 35 hours runtime, extended to 45 hours with solar charging – a feature not offered with the new Edge 1050.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Edge 1050’s display is 3.5 inches diagonal, the same size as the Edge 1040’s, but it offers a more vivid screen with greater colour usage. As well as touchscreen operation, there are metal buttons and a replaceable quarter-turn mount.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new speaker offers more interaction, with enhanced prompts when navigating and during a workout, rather than the usual beeps. It also provides an electronic bike bell.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Garmin has included Garmin Pay, so you don’t need to dig in your pockets to pay for your mid-ride coffee and cake. It’s a first for Garmin’s computers, although Garmin has included Garmin Pay in its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/fitness-tracker-guide\" target=\"_blank\">smartwatches </a>for a while. It may not be as useful for UK riders as for those in the US though, as there are a limited number of <a href=\"https://www.garmin.com/en-GB/garminpay/banks/\" target=\"_blank\">UK banks</a> signed up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s on-device <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/the-best-cycling-apps-for-route-planning-and-navigation\" target=\"_blank\">course creator</a> functionality, which will route you depending on whether you’re riding on the road, gravel or on an MTB. The map display on the Edge 1050 will differentiate between tarmac and unpaved roads and alert you to an approaching section of gravel or cobbles – handy if you’re planning to ride <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/paris-roubaix\" target=\"_blank\">Paris-Roubaix</a> or its amateur <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/review/katusha-travel-a-taste-of-roubaix-video-and-gallery\" target=\"_blank\">Challenge </a>ride.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Enhanced Group Ride features  </h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"787\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-970x787.jpg\" alt=\"Garmin Edge 1050\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-970x787.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-300x244.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-768x623.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-1536x1247.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-2048x1663.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-750x609.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0003_GroupRide_Results-1140x925.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Garmin is going increasingly social with the new computer. When linked to your phone, it will offer in-ride messaging functionality in Group Rides, as well as providing live locations for riders in a group, in-ride leaderboards for climbs and incident detection alerts for group members. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll also get road hazard alerts for potholes and other problems that have been reported by other riders. You can add to the tally yourself for the benefit of other cyclists.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once your ride has finished, Garmin has post-ride awards for the rider with the fastest maximum speed, most time spent pedalling and other stats across your group.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Garmin says that it will be rolling out the new Group Ride features on its other current generation Edge computers soon.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Garmin Edge 1050 other features and pricing</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"798\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-970x798.jpg\" alt=\"Garmin Edge 1050\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-970x798.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-300x247.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-768x632.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-1536x1264.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-2048x1686.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-750x617.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/06/Edge1050_HR_front_0001_ClimbPro_metric-1140x938.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Other features highlighted by Garmin are inherited from its previous cycling computers, including training plans and training status, in-ride stamina, power guides, ClimbPro and more, and there’s connectivity to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/garmin-varia-rtl515-rear-light-review\" target=\"_blank\">rearview radar </a>devices and to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/the-best-turbo-trainers-a-buyers-guide\" target=\"_blank\">smart trainers</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The UK SRP of the Garmin Edge 1050 is £649.99, an increase of £130 on Garmin’s previous top spec computer, the Edge 1040, or £20 on the Edge 1040 Solar.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-it-s-better-without-gps\">Opinion: Cycling is better without GPS</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tutorials/turbo-trainer-workouts-to-improve-your-cycling\">Best turbo trainer workouts to make you a stronger cyclist</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-bike-computers-gps-computers-for-training-navigation-and-data\">Best bike computers with GPS 2024 for training, navigation and data reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/the-best-turbo-trainers-a-buyers-guide\">Best smart turbo trainers: Top Zwift compatible indoor trainers</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-praise-of-the-cafe-stop\">In praise of the cafe stop</a>\r\n          